This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Country programmes are efficiently designed, coordinated, managed and supported to meet quality standards in achieving results for childrenÂ

description.narrative: In line with the United Nations Cooperation Framework (UNCF), the current country programme 2019-2021 was extended until 31 December 2022 in June 2021. A new Situation Analysis of Children and Women iis finalized, 91% action points from field visits and 90% of evaluation management response were closedy. Result-based management training for UNICEF staff was conducted in September 2021 to initiate the development of the new Country Programme, and more emphasis was placed on strengthening field monitoring. UNICEF contributed to the Sustainable Development Goals Data Landscaping Exercise to identify data available and priority areas for improving data availability.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:11/01/2022
